  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user I want my payment messages to work gracefully between different versions of the app.\r\nAs a developer I want to be able to add/remove selection of supported tokens easily\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n*Summary*: Receiving messages from future versions of the app should work reasonably well and without broken behavior and/or crashes, because future version sent a payment or request referring to tokens which are not defined in the older version on the recipient side.\r\n\r\nThis task involves creation of a contrived PR build which would represent a hypothetical future version with some tokens added and some removed. That build would then communicate with \"this\" build that represents the old version.\r\n\r\nFollowing cases can occur:\r\n\r\n1. Future sends/requests token A from Past and token A is  not known by Past. \r\n\r\nIn this case, Past should receive and display the message (even partially, possibly omitting e.g. fiat value) but indicate that token is not known. This unknown token should be distinguished from tokens which are known by the app, but simply not enabled in Wallet > Assets (i.e. #5500)\r\n\r\n2. Past version sends/requests token B from Future version and token B was removed from Future.\r\n\r\nIn this case, Future should display the message gracefully and indicate that the token was removed from the selection. It should be distinguished from not yet added tokens and tokens not enabled in Wallet > Assets.\r\n\r\nBoth cases should work with both ERC-20 tokens and native currencies.\r\n \r\nIf any changes are required in order to pass these criteria, they should be made in a separate PR and merged, while discarding the \"hypothetical future PR\".\r\n\r\nThis issue is equivalent to #6492 which deals with the same thing with networks.\r\n\r\n",
